  "prompt": "What are the best subject combinations to be selected in the arts stream for 11th?",
  "response": "Selecting the right subject combinations in the Arts stream for 11th grade depends on your interests, career aspirations, and the requirements of the universities or career paths you are targeting. However, here\u2019s a guide to help you make an informed decision:\n\n### **Core Subjects (Common for most students):**\n1. **History**  \n   - Provides a strong foundation in understanding societal, political, and cultural developments.  \n   - Useful for careers in law, civil services, journalism, and academia.\n   \n2. **Political Science**  \n   - Focuses on governance, political systems, and international relations.  \n   - Ideal for careers in politics, law, public administration, and international relations.\n\n3. **Economics**  \n   - Builds analytical and problem-solving skills.  \n   - Useful for careers in economics, business, finance, and social sciences.\n\n4. **Geography**  \n   - Offers insights into physical and human geography.  \n   - Relevant for careers in environmental studies, urban planning, and GIS.\n\n5. **Psychology**  \n   - Explores human behavior and mental processes.  \n   - Ideal for careers in counseling, social work, and psychology.\n\n6. **Sociology**  \n   - Studies society, social structures, and relationships.  \n   - Relevant for careers in social work, public policy, and research.\n\n---\n\n### **Optional Subjects (Choose based on your interests):**\n1. **Fine Arts / Visual Arts**  \n   - For students interested in creative fields like painting, sculpture, or design.  \n   - Useful for careers in graphic design, animation, and fine arts.\n\n2. **Literature (English or Regional Language)**  \n   - Enhances communication, analytical, and critical thinking skills.  \n   - Ideal for careers in writing, journalism, teaching, and publishing.\n\n3. **Philosophy**  \n   - Explores fundamental questions about existence, knowledge, and ethics.  \n   - Useful for careers in law, academia, and public policy.\n\n4. **Home Science**  \n   - Focuses on nutrition, child development, and family studies.  \n   - Useful for careers in hospitality, nutrition, and social work.\n\n5. **Legal Studies**  \n   - Provides an introduction to legal systems and principles.  \n   - Ideal for students aspiring to study law.\n\n6. **Mathematics (if offered in your Arts stream)**  \n   - Useful for students considering careers in economics, business, or social sciences.\n\n---\n\n### **Popular Subject Combinations:**\n1. **History + Political Science + Economics + Sociology**  \n   - Ideal for careers in law, civil services, and social sciences.\n\n2. **Psychology + Sociology + Political Science + Fine Arts**  \n   - Suitable for careers in counseling, social work, and creative fields.\n\n3. **Geography + Literature + Economics + Sociology**  \n   - Relevant for careers in journalism, urban planning, and public policy.\n\n4. **Legal Studies + Political Science + History + Economics**  \n   - Perfect for students aspiring to study law or work in public administration.\n\n5. **Psychology + Economics + Home Science + Literature**  \n   - Useful for careers in counseling, nutrition, and writing.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Choosing:**\n- **Align with Career Goals:** Choose subjects that align with your desired career path (e.g., law, journalism, civil services, creative arts).  \n- **Interest and Strength:** Pick subjects you enjoy and are good at.  \n- **University Requirements:** Check the entry requirements for the courses or universities you\u2019re interested in.  \n- **Balance:** Ensure a mix of theoretical and practical subjects to keep your options open.\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" combination is subjective and depends on your individual goals and passions. Choose wisely to make your Arts stream journey fulfilling and rewarding!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
